        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_ManualBillHeaderRetrieveManualBilling",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve records from a view named "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ManualBill.uvw_AccountManualBillingHeaders_ManualBilling",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". It filters the records based on optional input parameters related to manual billing headers, providers, and billing groups. The procedure supports pagination by allowing the specification of page number and page size."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves conditional filtering, default value handling, and pagination logic. While it is not overly complex, it requires a good understanding of SQL functions like "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ISNULL",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "NULLIF",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", as well as pagination concepts."
        }
      ]
    },
