        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Pagination",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure does not implement pagination logic in the SQL query itself (e.g., using "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "OFFSET-FETCH",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "). This leads to performance issues if the result set is large, as it retrieves all matching records before applying pagination in the application layer."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Default Page Size",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The default page size of 1000 be large for some applications, impacting performance if many users execute the procedure simultaneously."
